<div class="noinclude"><span class="script">template.XULRefElem()</span></div>
<p>A single column in a <span class="script">template.XULElem("columns")</span> element. Each child of the column element is placed in each successive cell of the <span class="script">template.XULElem("grid")</span>. The column with the most child elements determines the number of <span class="script">template.XULElem("rows")</span> in each column.</p>
<p>It is common to use columns only to define width and flexibility for the grid column and not place elements directly inside the column.</p>
<p>More information is available in the <a title="en/XUL_Tutorial/Grids" href="/en/XUL_Tutorial/Grids">XUL tutorial</a>.</p>
<h3 name="Example">Example</h3>
<p>See <span class="script">template.XULElem("grid")</span> for an example.</p>
